sion to the study of revolution, which has focused mainly on explaining how states are overthrown.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aWomen revolutionarieszLatin AmericavInterviews. 0aWomenxPolitical activityzLatin America. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Central America.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271023809?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271023809423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271023809/original  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK